content.description: Haven't done this one but it looks pretty good. Joshua is the crack specialist so I expect it to be sustained probably in the 5.10 range and most likely PG. We were there doing Cognition that day and it seemed like they were working hard on this one. All gear to the bolt anchor.
content.location: Start left of Cognition app. 30' in a crack system. Several are there so pick the best looking one.

content.description: A nice face climb on good rock with the crux about midway.
content.location: Far right side of the wall.

content.description: Moderate climbing past several bolts gets to a ledge at the base of the dihedral. Swing into this with good hand jams and slick foot edges thru the crux. More face climbing with bolts goes to a 4" crack to the anchor.
content.protection: app. 6 bolts, single rack to 4", doubles 1" -2"
content.location: Left side of the Sky area, starts on a face with a bolt and goes into the right facing dihedral.

content.description: Begin off a ledge in the wide crack, a #4 fits best. This section is a bit grainy so be careful at the start. Lieback the start and reach high to a ledge. Mantle up and move left to the straight up crack. Fun moves thru here go to the base of the crux roof. Wild jams here, then move right on ledges to the anchor.
content.protection: several bolts, double rack thru 3", one 4", wires
content.location: Obvious crack system going thru a roof up higher.
